    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The practice and technique of applying designs in pigment on pottery, which are objects made of hard, brittle, heat-resistant and corrosion-resistant materials. Pottery painting is usually followed by firing of the pottery to make the design permanent.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000076143/Sparkes, Handbook to the Practice of Pottery Painting (1923, 2012 reprint)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>De praktijk en techniek van het in pigment aanbrengen van ontwerpen op pottenbakkersgoed: objecten van hard, bros, hittebestendig corrosiebestendig materiaal. Nadat pottenbakkersgoed is beschilderd, wordt het meestal opnieuw gebakken om het ontwerp definitief aan te brengen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109894/UvA Talen</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A prática e técnica de aplicação de desenhos em pigmentos em cerâmicas, que são objetos feitos de materiais duros, quebradiços, resistentes ao calor e à corrosão. A pintura em cerâmica é geralmente seguida pela queima da cerâmica para tornar o desenho permanente</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
